## Getting Started & Deployment

### 1. Prerequisites
- A running Kubernetes cluster (Minikube, Kind, or a Cloud Provider)
- `kubectl` CLI configured
- An active Ingress controller (e.g., NGINX Ingress Controller)

### 2. Deploying the Application

Apply the Kubernetes manifests in your cluster:

```bash
# Create the dedicated namespace
kubectl create namespace chat-app

# Deploy Database, Backend, and Frontend resources
kubectl apply -f k8s/db-deployment.yaml -n chat-app
kubectl apply -f k8s/backend-deployment.yaml -n chat-app
kubectl apply -f k8s/frontend-deployment.yaml -n chat-app

# Deploy Ingress routing rules
kubectl apply -f k8s/ingress.yaml -n chat-app
```

